[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-15T22:25:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A render of Voyager 1 in space.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oxDWNnXWTe6so6eSN9AkSW6zNwg=/142x0:1678x1024/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73410061/Voyager_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: NASA</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"lfigUT\">Voyager 1, the farthest human-made craft from the Earth, is finally sending back data from all four of its scientific instruments, <a href=\"https://science.nasa.gov/missions/voyager-program/voyager-1/voyager-1-returning-science-data-from-all-four-instruments/\">NASA said this week</a>. That means the agency is once more receiving its readings on plasma waves, magnetic fields, and space-bound particles.</p>\n<p id=\"GAz2yw\">Voyager 1 <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/17/24075646/is-this-the-end-for-nasas-voyager-1-probe\">stopped sending back good data</a> in November, and fixing it was fraught as engineers had to <a href=\"https://blogs.nasa.gov/sunspot/2023/12/12/engineers-working-to-resol", "id": 719929, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/15/24179265/voyager-1-functioning-again-nasa-deep-space", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NASA says Voyager 1 is fully back online months after it stopped making sense", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-15T17:21:31+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of the Twilight sitting on a bedside table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8gKYqriEM9KFiPvHd-oebZlxmFY=/0x35:1920x1315/1310x873/cd